Challenge: Implementing authentication and database flow
1.Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) Design

Implementing multiple user roles (student, trainer, institution, programme manager, monitoring officer) with different permissions was complex. Ensuring every endpoint correctly enforced server-side authorization required careful dependency design in FastAPI.

2.JWT Authentication with Role Embedding

Designing JWT tokens that securely carried user_id, role, iat, and exp required careful handling to prevent unauthorized access. Managing token validation across multiple endpoints added additional complexity.

3.Database Relationship Modeling

Structuring relational entities like:

batch_trainers (many-to-many)
batch_students
batch_invites with expiry and usage tracking
required careful schema planning to maintain consistency and avoid data duplication.

4.API Consistency and Swagger Validation Issues

Ensuring all request schemas correctly matched FastAPI validation rules helped eliminate recurring 422 errors during development.